d quadlets yet, please make sure to check our <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mlqWeLkG55U">;Nextcloud deployment using quadlets</a>;. We also ship podman-docker, which is a podman wrapper that can be used together with docker-compose, or at least once the fix for <a href="https://bugzilla.suse.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1215926">;Bug #1215926</a>; is released for SLE and Leap Micro.</p>; <p>;<a href="https://cockpit-project.org/blog/cockpit-298.html">;Cockpit 298</a>; container management interface noticeably matured, as I'm finally able to use Cockpit to manage all of my home workloads.</p>; <p>;<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/openSUSE/news-oo/master/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/cockpit-298.png" alt="Cockpit Update" />;</p>; <p>;Users new to ImmutableOS space (systems with read-only /root) are advised to read <a href="https://kubic.opensuse.org/documentation/transactional-update-guide/transactional-update.html">;transactional update guide</a>;. Users can also use <a href="https://kubic.opensuse.org/blog/2019-10-22-toolbox/">;Toolbox</a>; to install additional software without a need to reboot into a new snapshot, this comes especially handy for debugging where the reboot is not an option.</p>; <p>;We've made a short YouTube <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j8kWT7HSjbw&amp;list=PL_AMhvchzBacAxIOv3_lRHBRrIUNo6Abp">;playlist</a>; with a few tutorials on how to put Leap Micro to practical use at home.</p>; <p>;<a href="https://youtu.be/j8kWT7HSjbw?si=XfwlSUsDM6zoYHzV">;<img src="https://img.youtube.com/vi/j8kWT7HSjbw/hqdefault.jpg" alt="Watch the video" />;</a>;</p>; <meta name="openSUSE, Open Source, leap micro, hostos, docker, podman, selinux, cloud, containers" content="HTML,CSS,XML,JavaScript" />;
